hypotheses.hypothesis: Liposomal gel formulation of Upadacitinib reduces acneiform eruption side effects by minimizing systemic absorption while maintaining cutaneous efficacy.
supporting_evidence: Upadacitinib treatment showed higher rates of acne (15-17%) compared to Dupilumab in Heads Up study.
Acne events were primarily inflammatory papules on face and trunk.
Mechanism of JAK inhibitor-induced acne is linked to follicular unit intrusion.

meta.reason: Insufficient automated signal in SEP-02 (28 papers). Manual fact injection for RExSyn testing.
